reviews.text:
Beautiful place and so uplifting to walk in the footsteps of St. Elizabeth Seton.
The Chapel is a nice oasis in the heart of the city.
Loved it here! Our tour guide gave us a wonderful tour and even stayed overtime to finish. Definitely worth visiting.
Beautiful and historic place..very peaceful. If you've never visited, I encourage you to do so.
Sweet visit, specifically if you are Catholic you can probably appreciate more. Free tour free parking
Very interesting place to visit.
Church grounds has a graveyard with 18th Century historical figures - cramped but well maintained, old historic cemetery.
Great place to find solace
Great for history buffs. Edgar Alan Poe, General McHenry  (of Fort McHenry ) and more all buried here.

On the corner of Fayette & Greene (across form the VA) is the Westminster Presbyterian church, with the grave of Edgar Alan Poe. An unexpected opportunity to pay my respects, within a tranquil piece of Baltimore.

To my dismay, I don't remember the gentleman's name. But our waiter took extra time to discuss a proper wine pairing, and to describe in detail the wine he recommended. Coupled with excellent food and a beautiful harbor view, this was the perfect Baltimore dining experience. Everyone enjoyed their meals and our waiter was great (I wish I remembered his name). The views were great and it was a lovely place for a long awaited get together. I would visit here again and I don't like seafood!

Had dinner with a work colleague. First, our waiter was fantastic. He had a lot of insight and suggestions. He also went into great detail to describe the specials for the day as well as recommending a soup that was not on the main menu. The food was perfect (I had the fish and chips) as it was perfectly battered to not absorb a lot of oil. The views are great from the waterfront.

Good experience—came on a Sunday night, so it wasn't very crowded. Our server was warm, friendly, and very helpful in guiding me through the menu. The huge crab cake appetizer was delightful—I've never had crab so tender and flavorful. Unfortunately, the entrees were somewhat disappointing—I had a seafood medley that quickly turned cold in a somewhat bland tomato sauce (although the mussels, shrimp, and other seafood were all extremely fresh), and my dining companion had a Catch of the Day dish that was, again, good but not spectacular. Maybe it was just the entrees we ordered, but we were left slightly disappointed after the spectacular appetizer. Overall, however, the harbor view and our amazing server made this a good experience.

Great ambiance! Fabulous view!  Window seating and personal attention to details by our server, Logan. Wonderful anniversary dinner. Fifth year in a row destination and wonderful memories. Loved the food, as usual.

Have avoided this cliched, touristy place for years, but with friends in town, it was time to give it a try. Glad I did. Very clean, neat and bright on the inside with fabulous views. I was afraid the views would overshadow the food but fortunately I was wrong. I like the menu - simple but sufficient - dislike restaurants that throw everything possible on the menu - how can they specialize on a few good classics? 

Prices were lower than I expected - $15 - $25 for a lunch entree. I ordered the trout, soup and salad for $19. Soup tasted homemade, salad was fresh, crunchy, cool - simple, but just right for being prior to the fish. The trout was grilled and seasoned perfectly, and the portion was correct for lunch.

Friends had the lobster roll and flounder and fish-n-chips. I cannot eat lobster, but my friend was ecstatic over it - large portion too. The flounder was prepared as well as the trout, and I did have some of the fish-n- chips. How restaurants prepare the most basic foods is the telling sign, and that fish was perfect - crunchy on the outside, moist, tender and flaky on the inside - yum yum!

Lexington market gets a bad rap but i love it. There are so many fresh, cooked and baked goods to chose from. I love getting snowballs. Beger's devils food cake is the absolute best. If you try nothing else get this cake; if you're a chocolate lover, get this cake; just because it's Monday, get this cake!

To be honest this was a "different" experience, there were several begging homeless people in the actual marketplace, BUT I did however see several police officers in the building. LOTS of different foods to choose from as well as bakery items. Parked across the street in a parking garage and walked right over. An overall good experience and REALLY great food.

I had a ball at Lexington Market! It's literally a market that sells a lot of uncooked (raw) meats and seafood. They also sell fruit, vitamins, a lot of cooked food that was delicious ! I went on the weekend a Saturday to be exact it was a live band performing and people dancing! They do have a parking lot on site but it was overly crowded so I parked in the parking lot across the street if it wasn't for the parking I would have gave them five stars!

The market is not like it used to be too many drug dealers too many drug addicts they have nothing you want to buy in there do you need to clean up the place and used to be a nice place to go on the weekends to get what you need now there is nothing in there but a few stalls no one's paying attention to you have to literally find it on your own the only place that is the same and I still go is at the top and a full section where they have clams oysters and crabs that's where I go and I still enjoy it

It's Lexington market you either belong or you don't. Its safe, police everywhere, transportation is great, food from all over the world 🌎 cooked, uncooked, inexpensive, home cooking, or health food, bathrooms, cleaned all day, built in 1700's so you know it's rough, 4 stars The most colorful caricatures in Baltimore, or any big American city,free music, jazz, r&b,..... Call to see what and when, that's where I introduced my grandkids to live music and intercity life, the hard side, any body can go to inner harbour smile 😃

Accommodating and authentic. Unpretentious. The portions were great. On top of all that come out do not leave without trying to Ethiopian coffee which takes a little while to make but it's well worth it. Spacious and warm. I'm going to head back for their breakfast tomorrow.
Tabor is great, I love Ethiopian food and Tabor is a great spot to get one fix in. Love their samosas. Pretty delicious.

Baltimore has few Ethiopian places, and among them, I prefer Tabor based on my recent visit. The food is better than that of Dukem nearby by just a hair. I've never received good service at any of the Ethiopian restaurants in the area, but at Tabor they put in more effort - I came at an unbusy hour and they were still accommodating. The wait staff spoke almost no English, so that can make ordering hard, and if you don't know what you want to order here, you will have a very hard time. However, the food is very good, and they have the best injera I've had.
Amazing food. Best injera in town for sure. Service is awesome! A must go if you like Ethiopian food or if you are ready to try it.

Excellent Ethiopian restaurant with delicious and authentic food and a great, cozy atmosphere.  Food might take a little longer than at some other places but Ethiopian cuisine is meant to be savored and with good company.

I've been to some pretty subpar restaurants before. That being said, this one took the cake for most bland food as well as horrific service. 

Waitress took it upon herself to blatantly ignore me when trying to order. Even after ordering, she threw the receipt at me. Still, trying to be a respectful human, I dealt with it. When the food arrived she didn't speak just slammed it on the table. When my son and I began to eat l, we looked at one another in disgust. All in all, nothing was enjoyable about the service or the food. There are better places to waste $34.

I love reading the reviews saying this is the worst Chinese someone has ever had. First off, you're an idiot if you don't realize that this is as authentic as you can get. Secondly, that food you eat is definitely not Chinese. That said, the atmosphere isn't great. The service was fine but nothing spectacular. But honestly the food made up for all of that. I'm definitely going back again.

The food tasted pretty good and the service was great....but I won't ever go back because the environment is beyond weird. You can tell its family owned. Which is normally fine but I felt it was TOO home like. I guess you'll just have to go see for yourself. I can't even explain it.
The food feels authentic (as far as I can tell) and is also terrific. Don't listen to the other reviews—the service is rather unpretentious (not a negative in my opinion), but the food is great.

Food was okay but was not really a dim sum place as advertised ie no carts and had to order. Don't go on Sunday at 11am. They really are not ready to serve at that that time even though they are open.
Good solid portions! There’s a lot of noodles and meat and plenty of topping to customize your pho. The broth wasn’t as flavorful as I thought and the meat was tough. Definitely had better
I've had both the beef and seafood pho. Both are great with plenty of noodles and meat. The seafood pictured below really hit the spot. I added sriracha to the soup for and extra kick on a cold day.
Ample portions and excellent variety of dishes to sample! Soup seems to be by far the most popular item.
Delicious pho and cheap the portions is huge, I wish they have a half of portion with a half of price
Pho ga, shrimp summer rolls... always good

This place is amazing! There were a couple figures and descriptions missing but nonetheless, the tour guide was knowledgeable and the museum itself has history! My dad took me here when I was little and I took my kids two weeks ago, the same figures are there and that's amazing to me! I do feel they need some funds to help preserve and update the museum.

This place is awesome. Very educational, informational, and evocative. Every black person in America ought to visit this place, and anybody interested in genuine history ought to visit too. It showcases the two sides of black history in America...the sad and the triumphant. It celebrates the achievements of many black people and even has some wax figures dedicated to Africa's exceptional leaders. Those wax figures are real enough that you'd think they were real people at every turn. The museum also covers America's unfortunate histories -lynching and Slavery. You think you know a thing or two about the History of slavery and yet a visit to the slaveship leaves one stunned! As for the lynching section, I just didn't have the stomach for it but I still visited. I was glad to see parents and their kids walk through the museum, and listened curiously to the kids' questions about the historical characters that they encountered. "Know thyself" is well said.
A great experience. I will be returning for as long as I am physically able. Great lessons of our history and excellent displays.

The museum itself needs work as its outside appearance doesn't do the history within its walls any justice.
It is however a place all African Americans should come to visit, the young and the old. Truly people from all walks of life should make it a point to visit this museum.  The history and the message that lives within these walls are profound. There is one exhibit that says...."Now we lynch ourselves!" Introduced by a sign that says..Blvd of Broken Dreams. This speaks volumes!!! Black lives do matter!! So if this is as true as the words itself, we need to love one another and stop killing ourselves and each other. This exhibit is powerful and worth seeing!  The tribute to President Barack Obama is beautiful. This museum holds alot of great knowledge about our history.  Inventions by black people that you may not even have about. It's worth a visit!

Love the place! So much history in the building does really open your eyes. Makes you want to be a better person and help others also.But building does need a remodeling job soon. Maybe we can all donate when we leave at the box so they can fix it up. Thank you guys for the history. We will be back!

I Love JOHNS HOPKINS Hospital. My whole entire family was born here down to my children, my sister children, etc. Every time I go here I am treated so good and leave feeling better! When Doctors hear im in the building they care for me so much. I’m very proud to have such great doctors. Here I know I’m in good hands always. Thanks JOHNS HOPKINS for birthing me out my moms wound and taking such great care of me ever since!

We have been in the emergency waiting room for 6 hours. Still waiting for the cleaning crew to clean a room so we can meet with the staff to discuss the lab results. The hospital needs to hire more people to clean or hire people who can work at a faster pace. Very frustrating. On the positive side the nurses in the emergency room are very nice and professional.

Best experience! Friendly and courteous staff, wonderful doctor, state of the art equipment, beautiful facility and the peace of mind from knowing that you are in the best hospital in the World. Thank you !

Your appointment line is horrible,  they keep transferring me to different numbers and when I was finally transferred to the right department, the lady said she couldn't hear me and hung up she didnt even give me a chance.  This happened after spending 22 minutes to speak with a rep. I hope someone reads this. I will never call this hospital again. And I was able to get an appt in 10 minutes with Walter Reed.

Waiting in the ER Rn playing on their cell phones talking to other people just socializing. No customer services skills my first experience at the hospital do not recommend.  If there too busy get pads (playing on there phone) had an attitude when ask if they had extra small adult diapers which she reply,No there to big for her I told her I get her pads in underwear. If that's not good enough for her then you can go CVS down the street.. 
 Mind blown like she wanted one someone to argue with her. Try to get her name. No name tag or badge.
Great crisp chicken love the 🍟 to 2/ 28/19
Great chicken and western fries. Awesome. service!
Awesome food,poor service.

The most delicious fried chicken and potatoes wedges! Also if you like fried vegetables... they have them! They also always have a few oriental dishes along with fried rice and lo mein noodles. Very nice people, family owned!
Best Hens on Earth!!!

Visited here while at John's Hopkins Hospital.  1 block West. These are the hidden gems I look for while I travel or in this case not far from home.  

Some of the best carry out food I've had in a while.  And is a big step up from the subway at the Hospital.  Had the Gyro the first day, but other had steak and cheese and pizzas.  Everything was delicious.  The gyros were not the best I ever had, but definitely passable.  

Went back a second day and had the Famous Deluxe Steak with Cheese.  Unbelievably delicious.  In the top 3 steak and cheese I have ever had anywhere. The steak was cooked perfectly.  The Deluxe has mayo, onions, mushrooms, green peppers, sausage  and pepperoni slices.  What a combination with such a great balance of flavors.   

I will definitely be visiting again when I'm in the area. I will also make a special trip whenever I want to experience this humble restaurant and carryout. It's 35 -40 minutes from home, but totally worth the trip.

Pizza is disgusting. Tastes like your biting into garlic and completely undercooked. We ordered carry out, they said 15 minutes; hour and 30 minutes later we were waiting inside for our pizza with no luck. Avoid this place at all costs.
Only been here a few times but I haven't been disappointed yet. I haven't had a lot of things on their menu but the orders I have had were great! Always busy but that's due to the great food.
Service is ok, subs are awesome wings normally taste old

It’s literally 2:30 AM you close at 3 AM. Every time I call the number provided on your website and on Google it says that the line is busy. That is unprofessional a restaurant should have a phone that has multiple lines.
Nice atmosphere, friendly waiters, and good food.
Mama Mia is a reliable chain; you can virtually guarantee good service and great food at sensible prices.
Lovely pizza offered. Recommended
Very nice place. Italian food. Good quality, staff very friendly and flexible with the menu. I recommand
Nice new location

All different types of culture food and flavors to choose from. High quality and fresh produce is top of the line. Price range from cheap to high but it all boil down to what you're looking for. If you want the best than expect to pay a little extra, other than that it's a wonderful market...
Great food choices. I have my favorites. I invite you to find yours too. Don't forget the fresh fruit.

Northeast Market is very clean.   I went to get a BLT Sandwich from the 3rd stall on the right side of the market off of Monument Street.   As long as I have been going there,  I still do not know the name of the restaurant. I tell you what,  the BLT is "SUPERB", leaves a unique taste in your mouth.   They have to be using,  OSCAR MEYER BACON.   That is the best tasting bacon around and then he paaaacccck's it on your sandwich.  The lettuce and tomato are always fresh and crisp.   The Kaiser Roll is delightfully fresh.   There you have - - - a Scrumptious "BLT Sandwich"...
I mostly visit the North East Market to purchase a Delicious sandwich from the Jawa Market or a great dessert from the bakery, or some delicious fruit and veggies from Richardson's Farm.
Great place to grab something to eat, drink or dessert. A wide variety of food to pick from. Also some little stores with different products for sale. Will definitely go back. Our lunch was great.

I got a chicken box with shrimp. The food was a little soggy by the time I got home, however it was still good. So flavorful and the sauce for the shrimp is good. I dipped my chicken in it. Not sure how I’m just finding out about this place especially since I’ve been at Morgan for two years now.
Food so bomb been eating here since I was a lil girl Baltimore’s Best🤷🏽‍♀️
Easily one of the best chicken boxes in Baltimore sunnys sauce is good if u into that kinda thing 🤷🏾‍♂️

The food was fresh and the service was fairly quick.  I was there at noon and didn't have to wait overlong for my order.  I wish the wings were cheaper but I appreciate the size, tenderness and flavor.  It's a good neighborhood spot to stop in and take out.
Great place to grab a chicken box and a half & half! They also have a lot of other menu options as well.

I looked around to find the best cake for my daughter's 5th birthday, at a good price. They exceeded my expectations. They have my business. The icing was not to sweet or over colored. The cake was moist and delicious. Definitely a place to get special cakes made.

Great customer service. Little more pricey than I expected. Everything is delicious and made fresh right there in the back. I will revisit just hope the prices are a little lower especially on the sale items.
THE BEST! My son loves their cookies and I love their everything! All of their cakes are fresh. Every time we have a party, I can count on Woodlea Bakery for a perfect dessert.. or two!
Absolute BEST strawberry shortcake on the planet..jus wish there was easier handicapped parking..the parking situation keeps me from enjoying that cake more often !!
Swing by this classic bakery for some of the most delicious treats in Baltimore!

Honestly some of the best pizza in all of Houston! I went down there for the park and saw this was the cheapest closest place so I gave it a try. I knew immediately that it was good because how good the restaurant smelled ,I bought a large pizza and almost ate the whole thing by myself! I definitely plan on going again!

Love the taste and size of the pizza slices!!! They have several different ingredients. The pizza sauce is A1! The sitting is limited downstairs but they do have upstairs sitting, so no worries if you enter and see small space. It's worth eating there!!!

I've been coming here for years! They have the best pizza spot in town. The pizza slices are huge. They stay open late , so I come here right after bar hopping. Warning: The place is small and is always packed. The place is always warm to hot. They have the game on 24/7 best place to chill and get some pizza.

I thought there would be on options for single slices,  there were only 4 different types..pepporoni, meat, cheese and supreme. My husband really liked it. I've had better crust before but not bad for the price.  Sorry no pics
Great pizza. Served by the slice or be the whole pie. Great service and friendly employees. Fantastic location. I highly recommend

Just go and eat crab cakes. You will definitely not regret it. Best crab cakes I've had in Baltimore. Laid back atmosphere, nice service, and great food. Call ahead and make a reservation. I called 2 hours before going to make sure they weren't fully booked and was able to get a table.

Their crab cakes are the best in the world. High praise from a born and raised Baltimoron. They're all meat minimal filler and huge! They almost entirely fill the 16oz container they come in. They're super fresh and even last a while if you need to store them before you devour them. If you eat in, the staff is friendly and accurate. There's not a ton of seating though so call ahead if you have a big group.

The best crab cakes in Baltimore, hands down! You might have to ride around for a few minutes to find a decent parking spot, but its worth the walk. The staff are super friendly and if you visit often, they treat you like family.
Service was great. I definitely will be going back. Best crab cakes I’ve had so far.
Great, no excellent grab cakes. Huge! All lump crab meat! Service good too. Will be back
Love these guys, the Pate is the best I've had and if they have duck, get it! I'm so happy they have reopened!  I've never had a bad meal here.

I enjoyed their restaurant before it closed and so I eagerly sent them an inquiry about having them cater a surprise party i was planning. The same day I got an e-mail from the owner stating how much he enjoyed smaller events and how excited he was by the prospect of my party. He also stated the catering director would be in contact with me in the next day or two.

A week passed during which I didn't receive any contact. Not by phone or e-mail (and, yes, I checked my spam/junk folder).

A few days after that I e-mailed the owner to tell him I hadn't been contacted and that I would be going with another caterer. That was five days ago and there has been no response to that.

The owner may be excited by some opportunities but the catering director appears less so. And no one seems interested in following up when inquiries get passed by.

It appears to me they have more enthusiasm than ambition.

Try them at your own risk.

The food is delicious. But the entire staff is horrible. RUN AWAY if you are considering them for catering. Irresponsible people who will mess up your menu at the tasting and not fix it at the event itself. Then, when you try to follow-up about refunds for food from the menu entirely never served, they will not reply to emails or phone calls. Once you reach someone by text message, they will blame their own colleagues for the problems and try to say they have no responsibility for what happened. Disgraceful, disrespectful, and embarrassing.

$$ p/person.  Winter Squash Soup and Crab Soup were amazing!  Licked the Bacon Wrapped Meatloaf plate clean and the Bluefish main course was also "yummy".  German Apple Cake is a must for dessert!
($ = roughly $10.00)

I called to make a reservation 30 minutes before and got there 90 minutes before closing time on a Saturday night only to find out the kitchen closed after we were seated. I told the fella I was leaving down town bmore n wanted to be sure we could eat there before we left. He said yes on the phone, seated us, then announced the kitchen was closed. We ate at Silver Queen Cafe. Go fund me and you turn away business long before closing time that YOU TELL IT'S OK TO COME AT 9:15 TO ORDER?   Taking money via go fund me won't fix this.  I picture Silver Queen Cafe in its place.  That meal was excellent.

I really liked it when they did a one act play there, Box and Cox/Double the Rent.  Need to do more of them.

The Gift Shop is really nice but they need to add new Items to it.

I don't know if they changed the hours of staying opening but closing the place at 4:00 in the afternoon is to early.  It needs to stay open until 8:00 or 9:00 at night on Thursday to Sunday.  Not everybody can be at Fells Point at that time.
Good place to stop by and get suggestions for Fells Point and Baltimore
Nice video to watch.  Close to some lovely local shops and cafes.  Right on the Quay side
An amazing FREE spot in the quaint neighborhood of Fells Point.  Well surpassed my expectations and kept my little fella busy with the hands on activities.
Wonderful experience

An absolute jewel of downtown Baltimore!! I found this museum by chance while going to lunch with my wife. It was a treat and historical gold for anyone in Baltimore. To see such history that resonates with the city of Baltimore specifically and cover national historical facts as well was awesome. The wall that paid tribute to young artists from competitions in local schools was inspiring. Very well kept, informative, excellent price of admission, validated parking, nice mementos in the gift shop. A wonderful experience for the family, insightful conversation starter for dates, and a point of pride for all African Americans and Baltimoreans of any race!

I went there on a university field trip for Black History Month, and it was such a good pick. There was so much information not taught in classrooms. I walked away learning a lot. The art exhibits were a wonderful surprise because I love art. They showed a few high school pieces, which were all incredible. I felt so inspired and motivated after viewing there pieces. 
The location of the museum is perfect. It is right next to Little Italy, and a short drive from the Inner Harbor. It's a great destination if you plan on visiting Baltimore

I take my son there for the Martin Luther KING activities. I liked how they had something for everyone. It's very important to me that my son understands the great work Dr. King started and it's up to us to continue that work. My child deserves the best no matter his color, and we will continue fighting for our God given right for equality, no matter who states differently.
I really enjoyed this museum. Very informative and the visual models were done very well. My only complaint which may be a work in progress but the middle floor seemed pretty bare.
They generally have a great exhibit. I really appreciated the kids events and activities when mine were small. Now I can also appreciate the youth events and adult evening activities.

Food was excellent, some of the best itallian food I've ever had. Definitely the place to go in Little Italy. Our server, Jake M was AWESOME, very friendly and professional even though he was dealing with a huge party of 10+. I will definitely be back!

Loved Amicci's! Staff was unbelievably nice, service was even better! I ordered the penne, my mom had the gnocchi with vegetables. Lunch portions are filling, and delicious. We had lunch at noon on a Friday and were out in under an hour, without rushing.  I wish I had thought to take a photo. It is casual, and comfortable.

Just ok, food wasn't bad but didn't particularly knock our socks off. Wine was pretty mediocre at best. Biggest issue was someone in our party ordered a chicken dish which came with pasta but received a dish with only pasta. Chicken showed up about 30 minutes later, oops. Service was pretty good at first but tapered off significantly, our server appeared to have a lot of tables on his plate.
Love this restaurant!  Food is delicious, staff is helpful and knowledgeable.  Recommend this to anyone looking for Italian food downtown!

Can’t say enough good about amiccis! Actually phenomenal service, food, and a great atmosphere. We had a party of 10 with nothing negative to say from any one of us! Even the young wait staff was super outgoing and refreshing. We’ll definitely be going back.

They stayed open longer after I arrived in town later for a conference at the Marriott. My hotel suggested this place and it did not disappoint. It was delicious and the lasagna was a large portion. Very reasonable in price. If i am ever in this part of Baltimore again, I would highly recommend this wonderful Italian Restaurant.

Fabulous food , decor and service. We were on a tight schedule and they were able to accommodate us without making us seem rushed. The Italian wedding soup was delicious as was the Chicken Parmesan. The best house salad I have ever had and I eat out a lot!
I left my credit card there and the owner went out of his way to overnight it to me. This is definitely my go to restaurant in Baltimore!

We were in Baltimore for a wedding. Discovered Dalesio's of Italy as it was close to our hotel. OMG! It was the most amazing Italian food. As if you were actually in Italy. Service was excellent! We basically had Valentine's night on 21 March and did not plan this. Dalesio's of Italy gave us a romantic evening😁

The penne alla vodka was mind blowing. The atmosphere was calming and the decor was classic and charming. The service was excellent and the meal did not feel rushed at all. Our waiter, David, was personable and took an interest in us as people instead of just patrons. If you're looking for an Italian restaurant with an inviting atmosphere and authentic, extraordinary cuisine, Dalesio's is the place to go. I would highly recommend this restaurant to show someone the beautiful things that Baltimore has to offer.

Absolutely amazing meal. 
Everything from appetizers to dessert were delicious. Definitely would recommend to anyone and would return here next time in Baltimore.

My wife and I just finished the most amazing meal! We decided to celebrate our 21st anniversary here.  Everything that came to the table was delicious. We had a grilled romaine lettuce appetizer that tasted like a steak! We will definitely be back. Our waitress Delia made our dining experience feel nice and slow and was very attentive to our needs.

The service was amazing, drinks and wine selections were perfect, appetizers were solid. Two of our dinners, pasta dishes, were perfect, the veal parm was not good at all. Been to tons of Italian places, worst veal yet. La Scala is an absolute gem in Baltimore's Little Italy. The ambiance is old school romantic Italian - dim lights, exposed brick, dark wood, and white table cloths. But don't let the classic feel fool you. La Scala is anything but stuffy. The menu includes modern twists on Italian classics and the servers are friendly, knowledgeable, and eager to offer their suggestions and answer questions. In addition to their sizable printed menu, there are numerous creative and enticing specials every evening.

So good.  Loved the Risotto. A little fancy for our family but the kids loved the ambiance and service esp.  the huge pepper grinder.  Everyone left well fed and happy.  Great little bocce grotto downstairs.  Wish I knew how to play.

Great food. Wasn't happy that they tried to stick us next to the kitchen but I asked to be moved and they moved me but the seat was in a walk way. The food was good I just thought it was too crowded to enjoy. There are other places just as good that aren't trying to squeeze you into a shoe box.

This food is so good. . . I hate savory grits but these grits are to die for. The potatoes are also to die for. The atmosphere is amazing. I tend to be   picky about food. This Italian restaurant is  worth it 100 times .

What an experience! Attman’s Delicatessen has one of the best corned beef sandwiches in Baltimore. It’s incredible and certainly one of Baltimore’s finest. Great atmosphere, wonderful service, and friendly staff. Well done guys. I’m going to be back.

Great food, and a really great experience. This place is a melting pot of every skin hue, religion, and political preference. Everyone stands in line and places their order, old fashioned corned beef mostly. Do not miss this institution.

Hands down the best corned beef and pastrami in Baltimore and the east coast-I like it better than Carnegie Deli in NYC personally.  Great staff and the place is packed so it's all fresh and delicious!  One of three places you must eat at when in Baltimore!
Such an experience for those not from the area! Loved classic and traditional deli vibe you get, not to mention the true to form NY Deli sandwiches! It's a must if you're in the Charm City
Baltimore's finest. Food is always great!  Staff is always friendly and quick. Great atmosphere. Love this place.
Delicious treats! The flavors change frequently. My personal favorites are cinnamon, black tea, and Bosc pear. Around half of the options are sorbets.
Really good gelato, like really good - a little pricier than some other places but definitely worth it
Yummy!! I would recommend trying the cardamom flavored gelato if you're not sure what to try. The servers were nice and efficient, and the place is quite clean.
Pricey for a small bit of gelato but SO GOOD. Love the chocolate hazelnut, pistachio, espresso, black tea, everything!!
Best ice cream I ever try. Specially chocolate-hazelnut ant pedtacho. Drinks are great

Cute little breakfast nook - a little packed, but well worth the trip. Had the creamed chipped beef and was impressed. Coffee was good and refills were plentiful. Servers were kind and attentive. My date had the Captain Crunch French Toast and enjoyed it very much. Happy we stopped in!

Food was incredible  , just loved the Capt crunch french toast w/ fruit.  I would go back in a second , this  place could  be bigger.  We were lucky not much of a wait  , but folks after us waited about the whole time we were there. It also feels like you are sitting on top of the next person.  Just to put this out there , if you have little kids , the language is not kid suitable if that is a concern to your family.
No wait time considering they had a party with 3 tables. Easy to see from the street. Trendy crowd. Small tables. Beautiful art. Great service.
We love this spot! Quaint place, filling food, and easy service. Definitely worth the visit and wait.

45 minutes wait for breakfast!  I am not addicted to food but we had time so we walked around. Food was good. Keep your expectations reasonable. Sweet Baby Jesus is their speciality. It was good but why that name!  When I was paying the bill at the counter,the staff was laughing as someone on our table was overdressed for their location and asked the server if they served any alcoholic drinks. None of that bothers me, but I can see it bothering people who are little sensitive about such stuff. 
My advice is if they seat you quickly go for it. It’s not worth 45 minutes waiting. Nothing ever is!!

Great little place with amazing atmosphere. The wine pairings are excellent and the food menu, though small, has something for most everyone. I cannot overstate how cozy and intimate the dining area feels. My wife and I have anniversary dinner here every year.

The great neighborhood bar/restaurant everybody wants in their neighborhood. Good food, good drinks, friendly bar scene. Henninger's has a small dining room, so reservations are recommended, but bar dining is less intimate and more fun.

A hidden gem in Fells. Food was amazing, bar atmosphere was quiet and perfectly lit...great for a date night with a new person or partner of 50 years. Bartender was extra friendly. Will definitely be going back.
Best place in town for Dinner especially with out of town guests to give them a taste of Baltimore that isn't some crab house. Their MD crab soup, crab cakes, shrimp, and steaks are all amazing.

Absolutely delicious veggie curry!!! The sold sooo many whole fish were sold, where they were out so this was my second option and i loved it! Very close quarters with fun and friendly staff. Will definately come again if im in Baltimore

We had our company dinner at Bar Vasquez last night, and it was absolutely fantastic!! The private event coordinator, Charisse, is AMAZING, and really easy to work with. She went above and beyond to set our dinner up perfectly. The restaurant is beautiful and the food was fantastic!! I can't wait to come back to Baltimore to eat at Bar Vasquez, and I would highly recommend it!

I just love this place! So romantic. It’s nice having a different option in town other than French, Italian, or seafood. 

I had a great Happy Hour with my friends with a fab menu and the bill was so affordable. We will be back!
Superb!! Fantastic atmosphere, drinks, and food, and the service was great - made for a very enjoyable night out. Everything we had was wonderful! Can't wait to go back.

Beth, our waitress, was awesome. Every single dish that we had was fantastic - and we had a big party. Gnocchi was delicious. Everyone who ordered steak said it was perfectly prepared. In town on business but will be back whenever the opportunity arises.
Great steak and atmosphere. We hosted an event and the staff was extremely helpful. All of the food and appetizers were wonderful.

One of the coolest museums I've ever been in. All sorts of amazing art and interesting stories/artists to go along with them. There are multiple buildings, each packed with art (some restrooms even have pieces scattered on the walls), all of which can easily make for four or five hours of entertainment. There's a great shop attached as well, which sells merchandise for the museum and all sorts of amazing thrift-store knickknacks. I would come back to Baltimore just for this museum!

I love this museum. Such amazing works of art. I had no idea they were having an Alex Grey exhibit. He's one of my favorite painters and it was amazing to see his full size work in person. If you go, be sure to check out the Lusitania made from almost 11,000 toothpicks and the fart exhibit downstairs
Love it. Parenting exhibit they have right now resonated on so many levels, definitely check it out! Gift shop is always a fun treasure hunt too. They have awesome vintage style posters :)

One of the best places to take friends and family visiting Baltimore, it's one of the best art museums I've ever been to. It captures all of the quirkiness of the city and highlights artists you won't find anywhere else. While it can be tough to swallow the entrance fee with some of the other free museums in the city, it's well worth it. Plus it's right next door to Fed Hill which is a great place to sit and watch the harbor from. In the summers they even screen movies against the AVAM so people can watch from the hill, and the entrance fee is waived for a few hours before the movie starts.

I absolutely loved this place, the art was quirky fun colorful and just so interesting, I wish I had a 
Whole day to go through each of them with depth, but I spent about 3hrs and it was just enough,  they have parenthood exhibition going on right now, pretty cool a very different perspective on art, the restaurant upstairs is closed, ever the restrooms were full of cool art pieces loved it, the store had some stuff to but i spent almost half an hour just going through the quirky store, a must go museum!!! Great for kids, young adults and adults
Historic Ships in Baltimore was a great experience and completely worth the money. You can easily spend half a day exploring these ships, and they're located near many other things to see and do.

There are several historical ships to see of all different styles and each with its own,unique history. Hours are slim 10-a very prompt 4:30 as are a lot of the Baltimore attractions, be sure to check days and times places are open as many are closed early or several days of the week.

Great looking ships. Only two were open when we went, the oldest one and the submarine. Both were amazing. They both included plaques that highlight various aspects and explain different sections. The submarine might be a bit too tight for claustrophobic people, but it was a great adventure for us and our kids. One thing I would have liked be improved is when they clean the ship’s deck. We arrived at around 11 and they were just starting to clean the deck, which was quite dirty. As they cleaned it, dirty water was making its was all over the deck. They should have done this before they opened. 

Otherwise, a great experience and will be back next time to see the other ships.

Cool exhibit in Baltimore!   Four historical ships and a lighthouse.   You can buy tickets to see one, two or all of them.  We did the pass to see all and spend a lovely couple of hours touring the ships.  Nice to go at your own pace and check out what is important to you.  Ships are well maintained!  Staff mostly friendly.
Very interesting and good collection of ships to visit. Great deals and prices for tickets.

Well kept, and fascinating, with very few places roped off that you can't enter. Doorways are low and stairways steep and tight, and if we weren't some of the only people there the claustrophobia would have started to set in, but it wasn't bad. Wonderful guides here too.

At Baltimore Inner Harbor but really wishing you could tour the inside of an old submarine? Well, look no further! The USS Torsk will meet any land lubber's curiosity!  The USS Torsk, permanently docked in Baltimore, served two wartime patrols during the last part of World War II. USS Torsk had the honor of being the last submarine to use torpedoes to sink enemy combatants of that conflict.  She served in the Lebanon Crisis and the 1962 Cuba naval blockade before retiring in 1968 to be a museum ship.
Was very cool to actually go inside. But there wasn't anyone there, literally walked all the way through and never met anyone. Tour with a knowledgeable guide would've made it much better

It's a WWII submarine ... how cool is that!

In great shape, a living piece of history worth the visit!

Easy to get to, get in and tour around.

The only downside- small gift shop, if you call that a downside.

Piece of American history and very well preserved sub. The sub was not crowded at all so we took our time reading and really looking at everything. Someone was even available to answer any questions you have.  A total of 4 ships are in the inner harbor and I definitely recommend checking out all 4.
USCGC Taney was my favorite of the Historic Ships in Baltimore. Definitely worth checking out and exploring this ship and it's important history.

This 1935 US Coast Guard Cutter (USCGC) saw action and successfully defended herself during the 1941 Japanese attack at Pearl Harbor!  She served in both the Atlantic and Pacific theaters of World War II, seeing much combat action.  Her last duties of World War II were to help evacuate American prisoners of war from mainland Japan. After her WWII service, she performed many peacetime Coast Guard duties and was called to action for the Vietnam War.  All in all, the USCGC Taney served over 50 years, retiring in 1986!
Great overnight program for groups (we went with a Cub Scout Pack.) Amazing history lesson, with some engineering flavor. Highly recommended.
A lot of history in this boat. It has served all over the world

We did the overnight experience with the boy scouts and it was absolutely fantastic. We got to stay in the bunks that sailors slept in, we did General Quarters drills, we did a simulation of the ship leaking and needing to be secured. We got to see the Engine rooms in detail and the guns up close.  We toured the bridge and the cic rooms. Very interesting and fun.  Got a lot of extra history and learned a lot.  Got to eat in the mess and tour many other components. If you get the chance to do this, I highly recommend it.

Our family loves the Maryland Science Center. We received a membership as a gift at the end of 2017. The displays are great and interactive, which keeps everyone entertained. The shows are well-done and informative. The planetarium offers a variety of informative and entertaining shows. Discounted parking options are available for members.

Maryland Science Center, we loved the dinosaurs in the Science Center that seems to be the main attraction. Ticket prices around $25 a person for an adult. We checked out the rest of the Science Center and it seems to be more for just kids not really for adults. Still was worth going and seeing the dinosaurs. And the harbor is very beautiful outside the Science Center. the prices are a little high for the food court $3.50 for a water  for a water bottle. But worth it if you like dinosaurs.

Nice science museum with lots of hand-on activities for children,  especially age 7 and up.  Nice dinosaur exhibit, good space and science area, and good area for brain and human activities.   
Big and spacious 3 floors with plenty of room for the kids to run around.  Will definitely take up a couple of hours of your time.

The exhibits were very nice and hands-on, and it's a good place to bring children. The dinosaur exhibit is especially interesting. However, there were many children today, and they sometimes interfered with the hands-on activities. This made it a little hard to enjoy the exhibits. However, I will still come back.

The Maryland Science Center was extremely entertaining and interactive for an adult. I was lucky enough to enjoy the Dollar Day in December (yes, just $1.00 to visit this super cool place) when I visited the harbor with friends. My only suggestion to the MD Science center is please advertise your events on the Visit Baltimore page. This is an awesome place with many free events (like every Friday Night Stargazing) and a great way to get your inner kid out!

The place is way more than just a view from the top of the world and everyone should visit if you haven't been. It has some good information about Maryland and people from there. It also has a really nice memorial in remembrance of 9-11.

Great Views of Baltimore City. It is worth the money. Honestly one of the best things to do in Baltimore. The 9/11 memorial is great at honoring the lives that we lost on that horrible day. Great place to take the kids! The elevator sure is an experience!
Amazing views. I got to learn a lot of Baltimore history and identify some key landmarks. Got a good price through Groupon right now. Must check it out

The view from up there is absolutely amazing! The cost is a little steep for the few "attractions" they have up there. It was chilling, because when you got off the elevator was a re-account of September 11, 2001. There's an amazing view of five different sides of Baltimore. You can see so far off in the distance. I definitely recommend it for anyone who just wants to sit there and take a deep breath and just be...
This is a really cool place to see the town and the harbor area. On a clear day you can see really far and a lot. I also like the all the artifacts they have from 9/11. Pretty cool place.
There chicken fettuccine is lovable I have to get it every time I go and it feels u up enough for two ppl if u haven't been u have to try it out...

Poor service!! We were hardly greeted when we walked in. This is our first and last time going to this place. The staff awkwardly buzzed around us like we weren’t welcomed & treated me like I was “supposed to know” how things worked there, just unfriendly all around. The waitress that brought our food over was FULL of theatrics as she breathed heavily on our food and told us she “was having chest pains” and was acting like she could barely deliver our food to our table. She acted like EVERYTHING was too heavy for her to carry but continued to stand and have conversations with the other patrons, sans heavy breathing and bad acting. My girlfriend even told her she should go to the hospital if her symptoms were so serious, but those fell on deaf ears as the waitress was already gone & wasn’t listening. I observed her serving the other non-Black customers without any difficulty breathing which furthered my frustrations. One staff member was so concerned about putting up Xmas decorations, that he couldn’t even open his mouth and greet or Check on customers. All around horrible experience. I took my leftover food to go because I liked the pizza, but after much reflection, I threw it away because I am completely turned off from this place!! 😒😞😒 racism is real & it doesn’t feel good. I’ll never patronage this place again. 👎🏾👎🏾👎🏾👎🏾 if I could give it 0 stars, I would.

Pretty good pizza but not the best. However, the place has charm and they work quickly and well organized when the cashier is not overwhelmed. My issue with the pizza is only that i literally saw no sauce at all on my slice. Light on sauce is one thing, but no sauce is another. Otherwise, great place!
Very good pizza.  Would definitely eat here again.  Would have liked more for the $ but very good.
Too much cheese, too soggy a crust. All the flavors are there with the sauce. Beats any commercial pizza but could be better so easily.

Delicious food (I tried the soft shell crab sandwich with fried green tomatoes and pimento cheese, side of grits... So good!). Service was top notch. Sarah was fantastic, plus a manager stopped by a few times to check in on me (it was pretty busy). Delicious drink menu with fruity options perfect for breakfast food, for a very reasonable ~$8 (especially when you consider it's in peak 'tourist tax' part of town). Photo is the bourbon peach strawberry lemonade. Yum!

Highly recommend!

Easily top 3 brunch downtown Baltimore, if you want to enjoy real Baltimore seafood and get a unique combination of flavors, Miss Shirley’s is the place to visit. All of the seafood has a clean and flavorful feel like it was caught the day before. Also, the popularity has grown so get there earlier than later. The lobby fills up with waits over an hour and there are two seating areas.

Going to be honest... This is my third time here and I've tried to give a fair shot, but it's nothing but disappointing. Not every time for the same thing though. This last trip, drinks and food was great, but the service guy just was not pleasant at all. The place wasn't even busy and the manager seemed frazzled and under stress. For the price, I expect much higher overall quality. Food was fine taste and quantity wise. Not sure a specific problem they need to correct, but it just doesn't work.

Per the reviews on YELP myself and my friend decided to give Miss Shirley's Cafe, Inner Harbor a try this past weekend day trip to Baltimore. The wait is very intimidating but it was well worth the wait!!!! And what can I say our dinning experience was AMAZING. Our waiter Billy was beyond knowledgeable about the menu and his recommendations were super helpful. I got the Avocado Toast with Pickled Shrimp and a Poached Egg and my friend ordered the French Toast and it was everything and more. Thanks for the great dinning experience. I definitely will be back on my next trip to Baltimore.

Delicious tasty breakfast which should have been 5 stars but staff was slightly disorganized. Our server was great but was "given" our party in the atrium while the rest of her section was in the main dining room. She apologized for that but it was necessary to flag  down someone else to top off our coffee. Speaking of coffee - my daughter in law had grounds in her mug. These 2 take aways dropped it to 4 stars. The menu is great and everyone enjoyed their food. Still worth a try..
