Favorite bar in Baltimore! Love the waterfront industrial vibe. Everyone goes when the weather is nice (so, crowded) but the coolest people go all year long. One of the best black bean soups I’ve had. Love love love

Best nachos I've had in a long time. We went during a rainy night, but even then the view over the harbor wan really amazing. It's right next to the museum of industry so we've already got a follow-up trip planned. They've also got a big parking lot which is a big plus in locust point.

It was my birthday. Its been 30 years since I've last visited this place and area. As a young woman I visited here to have fun listen to the music and be near the water. Later as a married woman with child is where I committed to bringing my children to a restaurant once a month. A tradition that continues in my grandchildren. Though the restaurant looked the same its heart was not. The greeting was business as usual sterile and slightly rude. The service was quick and efficient. The wait staff detached and awkward. Again it looked the same however it appeared to have no identity and no heart.

This place is Golden. The outdoor seating looks over the harbour and in the summer the breeze is to die for. I had the Cuban sandwich (my go-to) which was 👌👌. The brunch here is great also. If you like hot sauce try their special sauce they serve with the pork bites. So good.

This is a great spot for brunch and lunch, especially on a warm sunny day. The menu is reasonably priced. The food and drinks are really good. Try the Jamaican jerk wings and the pulled pork sandwich. Also, shout out to the bartender who waited on us. He was very attentive.

Loved it!  I have done in fine restaurants in big cities all around the world and I can honestly say that there are none better than Charleston in Baltimore.  You'll find that the food, the ambience, the service, but mostly the food! more than make up for the relatively high prices on the menu.  Treat yourself. It's an experience you won't soon forget.

Not knocking Baltimore. It’s a great town. But I never really considered it a gastronomic destination. Until now. This place confused my senses. Were we in Brussels? London? Madrid? From the moment you walk in, the staff treats you like you’re truly special to them. But it’s the food, really. Imaginative without being gimmicky. Prepared expertly and served in a quiet and elegant atmosphere. Oh yeah, this doesn’t come cheap. But you won’t feel like you’ve spent too much (well, at least you’ll feel you’ve gotten your money’s worth!)...

Everything about Charleston has been curated to offer excellence in every aspect. The atmosphere, the staff, the decor, and most certainly the food. Chef Wolf is, In my opinion, at the top of her game. The dishes are executed so beautifully and each course leaves you wanting more. You must get the wine pairings! The staff is incredibly knowledgeable and attentive. I can’t wait to return!

Great food, and great environment. The wine selection and pairing was superb. Everything was wonderful really but one thing. We went to Charleston a year ago, for a very special day. The only thing that has stopped us from visiting again is the waiter who was handling our table. He gave us a very bad feeling about asking about questions about the menu. It was my first time at a fixe menu restaurant so he sort of made fun of it. Only the waiter was like this though, the rest of the staff were great specially the wine lady who explained a lot about the gini wine in their menu That wine has become one of our favorite wines since then. Overall great restaurant, great food and wine, but the service at least for my case could be a bit more welcoming!

So amazing in every way.  Chef Cindy is a maestra of cuisine. Each dish is amazingly tasty and made with exquisite care. Every detail is attended to.  This was our fourth visit to Charleston and we are blown away every time.   Think of it as a mini-vacation, not a meal.

Food was excellent. I ate way too much. Don't fill up on the salad bar or sides. They are really quick to come around with the meats. Tables are close together but we were next to a couple of nice ladies so it didn't bother us. Our waiter was super nice.

Love this place. Staff is excellent. A bit pricey... You get what you pay for. Sign up on their web site and you can receive coupons/discounts. Best steak house in Baltimore by far. A lot of variety of meats and great place to go with friends and family. I had an amazing time at Fogo. The staff is friendly, the food is amazing and it’s an all around great experience. MUST GO!!!

I love Fogo de Chão, either Baltimore or D.C. are great. You might want to take with you a list of the meat cuts so you can make sure you tried them all after your visit. In some cases, you end up eating the same cut several times and you don't get to try other cuts. Never had a cold peace of steak. Servers are awesome, salad bar is great. The best Brazilian steakhouse IMO.

Top notch, napkins down, a good time! My friend and I went to Fogo De . The experience was great! the staff was responsive, quick to meet needs, and we even got a complimentary chees cake to celebrate. Would diffidently go back to celebrate more occasions. I had an amazing time at Fogo. The staff is friendly, the food is amazing and it’s an all around great experience. MUST GO!!!

5 star food, 5 star service. The staff was amazing, quick and ready to go. The self serve bar was really good but the meats, they were all out of this world. The service manager is a great guy, he spent some time talking with the table about all the different things they had, we missed one somehow. He had it brought out to us to try. That’s service you just can’t get anywhere else. We will be going back. It’s worth the trip if you can do it. Be ready to tap out however. The meat doesn’t stop coming unless you make sure the card is on the red. The hard part is, it’s all good. You don’t want to stop.

To my dismay, I don't remember the gentleman's name. But our waiter took extra time to discuss a proper wine pairing, and to describe in detail the wine he recommended. Coupled with excellent food and a beautiful harbor view, this was the perfect Baltimore dining experience. Everyone enjoyed their meals and our waiter was great (I wish I remembered his name). The views were great and it was a lovely place for a long awaited get together. I would visit here again and I don't like seafood!

Had dinner with a work colleague. First, our waiter was fantastic. He had a lot of insight and suggestions. He also went into great detail to describe the specials for the day as well as recommending a soup that was not on the main menu. The food was perfect (I had the fish and chips) as it was perfectly battered to not absorb a lot of oil. The views are great from the waterfront.

Good experience—came on a Sunday night, so it wasn't very crowded. Our server was warm, friendly, and very helpful in guiding me through the menu. The huge crab cake appetizer was delightful—I've never had crab so tender and flavorful. Unfortunately, the entrees were somewhat disappointing—I had a seafood medley that quickly turned cold in a somewhat bland tomato sauce (although the mussels, shrimp, and other seafood were all extremely fresh), and my dining companion had a Catch of the Day dish that was, again, good but not spectacular. Maybe it was just the entrees we ordered, but we were left slightly disappointed after the spectacular appetizer. Overall, however, the harbor view and our amazing server made this a good experience.

Great ambiance! Fabulous view!  Window seating and personal attention to details by our server, Logan. Wonderful anniversary dinner. Fifth year in a row destination and wonderful memories. Loved the food, as usual.

Have avoided this cliched, touristy place for years, but with friends in town, it was time to give it a try. Glad I did. Very clean, neat and bright on the inside with fabulous views. I was afraid the views would overshadow the food but fortunately I was wrong. I like the menu - simple but sufficient - dislike restaurants that throw everything possible on the menu - how can they specialize on a few good classics? 

Prices were lower than I expected - $15 - $25 for a lunch entree. I ordered the trout, soup and salad for $19. Soup tasted homemade, salad was fresh, crunchy, cool - simple, but just right for being prior to the fish. The trout was grilled and seasoned perfectly, and the portion was correct for lunch.

Friends had the lobster roll and flounder and fish-n-chips. I cannot eat lobster, but my friend was ecstatic over it - large portion too. The flounder was prepared as well as the trout, and I did have some of the fish-n- chips. How restaurants prepare the most basic foods is the telling sign, and that fish was perfect - crunchy on the outside, moist, tender and flaky on the inside - yum yum!

It’s your home away from your home, I spend a 3-months there, everyone was like a family to me, everything is available, mr.bill and ms.amy were amazing, available and always there to help you. 
It is a families friendly place. 
Safe place : there’s passwords everywhere. 
Clean place 
There activities for children also 
Books everywhere, toys and games for adult and children is available. 

I LOVE that home. 

❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

Very nice place comfortable and affordable however not very understanding when you have a small child that has a huge tantrum in the middle of the night. I do understand the need for quite however when a child is misbehaving it's very stressful in this environment. To add to the stress they jump to conclusions as to what's going on in the room as your small child has a level 5 melt down and your trying to get him to listen.  Just a heads up mom's don't put yourself and your small child threw this and stay someplace else. I'm sure alot of you  Mom's and grandmas can  Relate as most  small children can be a handful.

Such a wonderful facility!  They opened their doors for us in a last minute emergency and I will forever be grateful!  Right across the street from the hospital and so affordable!  We would have had to sleep in recliners in an ICU room if not for this place!
Great place to stay unbelievable staff. Amy is the best.
I was amazed! The personnel there was friendly, courteous, that made you feel like staying there would be your home away from home.

I'm only giving this restaurant a 5 because, if you are a true vegan you will appreciate the food. Menu has great options and is prepared with expertise. Very impressive with the creativity and thought process into opening a vegan restaurant. If you are not a vegan, to really enjoy it, just be open minded. And be aware the texture of food is different from previous diets.

My Mom loves the oxtails, Mac 'n cheese and collard greens. The peach cobbler dessert didn't look appealing so she didn't eat it. I will definitely be back for more.
It was heartwarming to see teenagers working the front and really showing what they can do when given the opportunity. Your company is definitely an asset to so many communities.

The Land of Kush definitely deserves 5 stars. I would recommend trying the curry chicken and macaroni. It tastes absolutely phenomenal. Excellent customer service and delicious soul food. I couldn't ask for a better dining experience.

I hate I forgot to take a photo of my first order—the vegan beef tips made with blackened seas with collard greens and homemade ginger tea. The food was quite savory! The picture below is of the lentil burger on a gluten-free bun, which is topped with their spinach salad instead of the usual: boring lettuce. The unique lentil seasoning combined with the tahini dressing on the salad creates a total food orgasm. They have many gluten-free options and a casual “spot” feel. I will definitely return.

I had the curry chicken combo meal with candied yam, carrot tuna, and the akoma smoothie. The curry chicken was amazing, and the other parts of my meal were close behind, although the carrot tuna was somewhat of an acquired taste. The staff was a little terse with me, but the restaurant was pretty busy when I made my appearance--and for good reason. Definitely the best vegan place in Baltimore that I've had the pleasure of going to!

Worst food I've ever ordered. I was starving and still left my matzo ball soup and half my corned beef Reuben sandwich. My wife ordered the beef shawarma on rice with hummus. She left hers as well. Red crab soup didn't have any crab meat in it to speak of. Maybe it was supposed to be crab flavored? TERRIBLE 
For $26 I feel like I was ripped off. 
I'm sticking with Captain James' Landing and crab cakes from now on or just plain old Subway.
All the food that I tried is really good, great spices. Would recommend to everyone.
Yummy, fast, and affordable! Plus 24 hour breakfast :)

Horrible experience. Was completely ignored by the owner. He was at the register, and asked if I had been helped yet. I said no. He proceeded to take the order of the people standing behind me! When another worker came up and said that I had been waiting, he actually said "no, no, I'm going to help these people behind her first. Then I'll get to her." He said that right in front of me! Seriously?! Get out of the service business.

Somehow I walked by here hundreds of times before trying their falafel.  Won't make that mistake again.  A bit on the small side, but truly superb.  Only reason I didn't give them 5 stars was that I also ordered a side of baba ganoush that was very good, but not on the same level as the falafel.  Excited to try out some other menu items.

Definitely a place to go. It’s very cozy, with big variety of options, and most important - good healthy soups. Prices are very very good too. First was worried about the portions, but soups are very nutritious so it wasn’t a problem. Sandwiches are good as well. Very nice place to hide from the city and enjoy warm meal
love love love this place. so convenient to work, staff is super friendly. Quick, efficient, caring. Lovely place. Prices are good, soups are always fresh. house salad is bombbbbb

As obsessed as I am with soup and the soup from this bistro specifically, this was my first birthday visit! I love this restaurant, the identical twin brothers who co-own it are 2 of my best friends whether they've pieced it together or not,  and it's quite literally the friendliest place in Mount Vernon! If you don't believe that last line, you can ask my fave bartender from Iron Rooster Canton, Antonio, and he will back it up since he tends bar at the friendliest restaurant on the Canton Waterfront side of the Harbor! Amen!
The owners are extremely nice and have excellent customer service, and the food is delicious. Their deserts are great too!!
Definitely one of Baltimore’s hidden gems. Delicious soups and wonderful service. Well done!

(This review is in regards to the downstairs). This place is fun! Menu items are serviceable. Don't go expecting five-star sushi, but the sushi definitely ain't bad either. It has a college-crowd vibe to it for sure, but not in an immature way. They have drink specials and on the right night you can get absolutely hammered for cheap. Only downsides: Sometimes the music is aggressively loud, and I don't get cell service down there.
Love this place. My second time visiting with my family.  Love the sushi very fresh. People are friendly service was fast. Drink specials and food specials awesome

This place has the best sushi I've ever had in the US of A. Now usually you might think someone is exaggerating when saying something like that. But nah. I mean it. I go other places hoping their sushi will be better and get constantly disappointed. Smh. An interesting problem right.

Went here for the first time after passing by it for years, and had a good experience! Good sushi, and the prices are great too! There is a large selection of both food and drinks, including beer, wine, and cocktails. There is ample seating and a large bar.

First time I came to eat here and it wasn’t disappointing at all. One of the freshest sushi places I have ever eaten at. Everything cooked to perfection, rice was perfect and not soggy. All ingredients were super fresh. Fish didn’t have a bad smell. Location is clean and I even saw they have a bar downstairs apart from the restaurant, but they will still serve you food if you want to drink and eat. Please keep up the good business running!

New location but same great food. Tasty options both for vegetarians and their meat-eating friends. Open face samosa offers the familiar flavors in a crunchy cup, mains have deep flavor without relying on the heavy cream that is too often used in other Indian restaurants.
I'm so glad this place has reopened! They have great people and the food is no joke! We've missed you Indigma! Welcome back!
Went for the first time this weekend and the food was incredible! Split a few appetizers and meals with a group and enjoyed everything we got. Highly recommend.

SOOOOO GOOD! Firstly their lunch buffet had tons of vegan options and the staff was so nice I felt like I was totally taken care of. Not just my server but like everyone was abnormally nice.The interior is gorgeous, it was quiet and clean! DEFINITELY THE BEST INDIAN FOOD IN BALTIMORE! Their options ranged from classic (lentils, etc) to really unique entrees I've never tried before.
Superb place to spend some Quality Time eating. I love the Vibe here and food is really Good and Service was Faster than I expected.

Kumari is delicious :) but they also have amazing customer service. I ordered from them through Postmates. They held onto my food for 30 minutes and when I called, they offered to send their own delivery guy to me free of charge. They do good business!

Went with my girlfriend for the buffet. It was a pleasure having lunch there. They have alot of space and a great layout for such a small building so we weren't sitting on top of other people. They also had a person at the buffet to help people who weren't familiar with Indian food. Food was delicious. Will surely be going back.
The buffet was really good. Price was good as well $12 you can't beat that.

This place used to be good. However, I feel like the quality of the food and service has gone downhill. The new female servers are rude and barely do their job. I heard Buddhi, the original owner, sold the place. Perhaps that is why things aren't like they used to be.
This is my favorite resturant in Baltimore. I love their super creamy version of chicken tikka masala. Their lunch buffet is delicious and an amazing value.
I'm always looking for good sushi. Sometimes it's a hit or miss but Minato never missed. I definitely recommend the Japanese bowls but nothing will defeat a good Nigiri Sushi. 10/10

Okay sushi and some good weeknight happy-hour type specials. I've had ease doing carryout and the staff have always been very nice in my experience. I will say some of the stuff here runs really expensive and I don't understand why. It's also not even close to the best sushi I've had but it's never made me sick, so.

Great sushi and cocktails, and awesome sushi happy-hour prices. Can get a little busy during happy hour, but it's usually not hard to get a table.

Edit: knocked 5 down to 2 because despite the sign saying they close at ten, we were refused service by the sushi bar staff before 930 and told they were closed. Check out Aloha Sushi just up Charles St and open until 11, but actually open until then.
Food is great and was very reasonably priced for us (esp during happy hour) - we love coming here for sushi, bento boxes, and poke bowls. Serving staff are very sweet too.

This is a great place to catch up with old friends. The tables are small but can be pushed together for larger groups.  The staff was very helpful in letting us know what the best rolls were and we left happy and full. There is not great signage so ask around if you have trouble finding it. Everyone on the street was very kind to us as we were a little lost.

There's something for everyone at City Cafe! I love the variety of appetizers and entrees, as well as their selection of beverages. There are areas of the restaurant that are quite chatty, as well as quiet if you're looking for a more intimate conversation. I've never had anything short of excellent customer service. I highly recommend the sangria and Morrocan burger! Very filling and healthy and not greasy at all.

Just awesome!  We had brunch there this morning. Andrew was our server and he was so nice. The angry omelet was very good. And the ambiance was fun, too. The only thing needing improvement was the coffee. Very bitter. Not sure if it was the coffee or the brewing, but something was off.

Went to brunch today with my wife for my birthday.  We have been going to city cafe for years and it’s always been a favorite.  Today was an awful experience.  Our appetizer never came (which we were most looking forward to), and my wife’s food was not only incorrect, but stone cold when it arrived.  My omelet was horribly over cooked.  We usually don’t say anything but today we did, and we got a ‘sorry about that’ from our waiter and that was it.  A $75 bill for inedible food was delivered with no offer of a replacement meal or the appetizer.  Have to say that will unfortunately be our last visit to this place.  We ended up at the owl bar eating pizza...which was fantastic.  Should have went there in the first place.

They forgot to microwave the crab cake enough (ice cold in center, seriously, others felt it and were disgusted) then they brought a "replacement" out on a dirty plate after we all finished our meals. . . 
. . . Regardless, it's a dying neighborhood and they don't care about cutting corners.  Just look at the feedback!  They won't even take a couple minutes to address issues or say thanks.  Just walk another block or two and have an enjoyable meal.

Nice laid back atmosphere. The food is very good and tasty. Service was fast and I did get every one of my requests for my food exactly right as requested.  Extra sauce for my  brussel sprouts and the blackened salmon was crisp  on the outside and tender on the inside. My my my!

We go here a few times a year.  Our go to for special occasions.  We have never been disappointed.   Always fantastic meal, outstanding service and great experience.   Hopefully this was a one time occurrence.  6 people, 5 prime ribs ordered.  Only one was cooked correctly.  They seemed to be reheated or older roasted ribs.  4 were ordered M-MR and we're delivered well done, exempt from any red at all.  They did try to make it right by bringing a new cut.  I just expect it right the first time and that everyone should eat together.  Timing was off.  Disappointed this time.

Love the atmosphere!  The food is typically consistent and service is always impeccable.  This time I ordered the clams and there was a lot of shell in every one of them, I was barely offered an apology for it.  I expect more from the Prime Rib.

This is not the place to go if you're on a budget. However, if you want to splurge, or you have the $$$$ to spend the night out, go for it. I had the delicious crab cakes, potatoes au gratin, potato skins, and hot fudge sundae for desert. Attentive waiters, free valet parking, piano music, low-volume atmosphere. I enjoyed my visit.

My wife and I were in visiting for the weekend . Whenever we travel we always try to find a nice restaurant to eat steak / seafood . After reading reviews we settled in on this place . I’m glad we did , everything was outstanding ! I had the prime rib and my wife had flounder stuffed with crab which she believes was the best she has ever had . There house salad was delicious and the creamed spinach did not disappoint . I tried the the potato skins with horseradish add on as a previous reviewer had mentioned . Phenomenal ! The oyster Rockefeller was also great . I liked there shrimp cocktail which I get just about anywhere I get a chance . This was the best food we had while in Baltimore . If I lived here I would be a regular there . I thought the food was reasonably priced for the quality of what you get . If I had to pick out any negative at all it would be the size of restaurant . It’s close quarters eating . Although for that food I would eat in the bathroom 😁.

We went for restaurant week. The prime rib was an extra surcharge ($5), which was not posted on the Baltimore restaurant week site. That was a unwanted surprise. Otherwise, service was slow and relaxed, which I liked. Food was good, but I would not pay full price for the meal if it wasn't on special this week. Dessert was excellent. Overall, it was a very good experience.

This is a great place and a great way to get a good sense of the babe and his life and accomplishments.  Knowledgeable docents really make the experience complete.  I actually return fairly frequently.

This was an excellent historical and learning experience for our family. We have driven to experience this museum several times from Lancaster, PA. Though this is a smaller museum, they have a decent amount of baseball and Babe Ruth memorabilia and exhibits. The exhibits are well designed, full of information, and many displays feature multimedia are interactive aspects.
Great place to visit. Very creative with what they were able to with such a cozy space.

Nice area well preserve. I Had a great experience going to the museum and keeping up with not only american culture but keeping up with american history. I good place to visit if you are in the neighborhood.
Very cool place and I got usefull knowledge from here.Good place to take your kids too. This is a great to know about different story, as well as different cultures from all over the world.

GREAT FIND!!!! Delicious food, great menu,  great prices,  super service, chill cafe atmosphere.... gonna become my go-to for sure!!!!
Menu has spot-on traditional hummus but also rotating special recipes: apple cinnamon raisin hummus this time was FABULOUS!!
Everything was fresh,  well seasoned,  beautifully plated and portions not too much but more than enough. 
Enjoyed the Salad Trio, and mezza Medley Plate, finished with fresh made cardamom coffee! 
5 stars all around!!!
One of a kind restaurant in Federal Hill area of Baltimore.  Can't miss with anything on the menu. Highly recommend the falafel as an appetizer.
Everything on the menu is amazing and fresh. One of my favorite places in Baltimore. The staff is very friendly and professional as well.

Such an amazing quaint place ! The food was fresh, authentic , delicious and well portioned ! And to top it all off byob! The staff was so friendly and informative about the menu. They were even so friendly when I left my purse there by mistake and had to come back to get it.  The owner was an amazing human and I can’t wait to come back.

Cute, quaint corner restaurant. The atmosphere is charming and the food is authentic, delicious and reasonably priced. It is also byob, so grab a bottle of wine before you head over for dinner. Seating is limited.

I loved them as a kid. Now they taste just like they look..like poopoo.
Would give them a zero if I could.

I am not originally from Maryland but on my return to Texas a native Maryland to ask me to pick up several packages of these cookies. I was curious and asked what was the significance of these cookies. The individual responded that if you have lived any time in Maryland, this was an opportunity to try something that is born and made in Maryland. So I bought an extra package for me and the family to try since they are made here in Maryland and I was already bringing two packages to Texas for a friend of mine.

As a native Marylander, I love Berger cookies. However, I was saddened to see that the chocolate topping is made with palm shortening, a derivative of palm oil. The practice for harvesting palm trees for palm oil destroys tropical forests and habitats of the animals who live there, so this is a definite turn off.

The cookies are outstanding and their customer service is awesome.  I contacted the company regarding a damaged shipment and immediately received an email from the owner with an apology and to let me know a new and larger complimentary shipment of cookies was on the way.  You cannot beat that for great customer service

Very delicious brand and god help us all if Royal Farms(small store for any non-east-coasters out there) ever went out of stock of them when you REALLY want them(always sold out, honestly...). Even when smushed or partially melted; great cookie for its taste and decent size. Packaging is decent and not loud or decieving, you can see right through to the cookie and the chocolate tastes even better than it looks!

The food was extraordinary. Absolutely delicious. Alcohol is also served. Great list of wines and beer. The service is prompt. Very clean and one of the most amazing views in Alexandria. Takes you back in time where traces of cosmopolitan Alexandria are more than just obvious. The decoration is fantastic. Prices are high, but you get what you pay for.

Would never hesitate to rate this restaurant as "perfect" and give it 10 stars
The staff are super nice, food is yummy and the venue is cosy
Expensive but deserves each pound
Highly recommended
Perfect place for lunch and dinner.
Great place for shisha
Very good decorations and food, yet it's a before sunset restaurant. It's problem is about the lack of variety in hot drinks and it's extremely high prices.

Miss Bruce Lee's World wide known chicken strips. Now the owners have gotten rid of Nick's.
 NOT COOL or Good!

I love this market always clean very minimal begging if at all maybe a few parking ticket hustlers but I can live with that this is the only place I go to get my meats fresh meats friendly patient staff never shows signs of frustration when I can never make up my mind very good shopping experience everytime
It's one of those places that you don't know about until a friend meets you there. There's also food, so plan on pretending like you know what's cool to eat.
Needs to be domilshed and start over. It's the Pitts!

I've been coming to the Cross Street Market for over 15 years. It is a real piece of genuine Americana. A lot of very vendors - nice blue collar place to go to. Now, it's under renovation and the market Administration has forced many of the vendors out. It's still neat, but they're going to Yuppie it up a bit too much I think. That's such a shame.

Great soul food! Chicken is a true version of rotisserie. Everything is deliciously season to perfection however they are often sold out. Be prepared to be disappointed when you walk in. The food is great that's the cause of often sold out. Customer service is great. Also you can sit and eat. You will spend about $13.00-$18.00.
Owned by the best. Delicious, affordable food! They do take credit cards. You can sit down and dine or take out! Enjoy, you will not be disappointed!

So i just had to write a review because of not only the awesome food, but the wonderful customer service that the lady at the register provided. The rotisserie chicken and corn muffins are awesome and she threw in an extra one because i waited. I would definitely recommend them!
Very good food and the people are very nice 💪

So Nick’s Sub shop is now called Nicks Rotisserie. Their rotisserie is easily the most distinct seasoned chicken that I’ve tasted. I’ve bought large amounts of chicken for two events and the chicken was all the rave for some very picky eaters. The cabbage is a tad sweet and I loved it.

Good Mexican food! 
It is worth going although It is a small place with a few stools. Plan to place an order before and pick it up later.
And be careful of parking. You'll get a ticket even for 10 minutes. Based on a true story!

Reuben's accomplished mixing Latino and French culture wonderfully. I highly recommend coming by or ordering online for date night. There is not much seating, but it's got a wonderful feel to it and is well worth it.

6 years ago a lone gentleman at the Baltimore farmers market sold me the best everyday hot sauce I've ever tasted. I had very much missed it so I am glad to reconnect after a few years, never stop bottling the sauce! 🤙🤙
One of the most legit Mexican spots in Baltimore. Everything I've tried is delicious.

Rubens is everything you want in authentic Mexican. It’s spicy, it’s savory, it’s sweet. The staff is incredibly genuine and know their stuff. Can’t say enough about this place. This needs to be on your radar.

Love this place! I've never had a bad meal here, everything I've tried is delicious. The wait staff is excellent and always friendly. Even my cilantro sensitive husband loves the food. For authentic Mexican food there is no better place!

The food here is always good, we have been coming for over 20 years. This is singularly my family's favorite restaurant. I would go as far as to say we are regulars. We have done many birthdays and special events here. The last birthday we did here was my sons and it was actually a few months ago. Tonight when we came in one of the waitresses came up to my son and ask him if he forgot something when he was here for his birthday party. She pulled out a birthday card that he had left at the restaurant with money in it. The fact that it still had the money in it and they remembered him. Was incredibly heartwarming. I cannot say enough good things about this place the food is amazing and so are the people!

This was my first time back to El Salto in about 10 years, maybe longer.  It is way different than it used to be, the renovation made a big improvement and it appears to be well maintained.  Food was fantastic and very reasonably priced.  Bar drinks also exceeded expectations.  Server and staff we friendly, accommodating, and were very attentive.

We will definitely be going back regularly.
Great service and delicious food!! Alyssa was a wonderful server! Definitely keep going back, been a patron over 3 years now. Highly recommend El Saltos!!
Food was great. Service was nice. Not authentic Mexican food. More Tex-mex style. But still good.
Great experience. Good food. Pizza is nicely sized, could easily split it with someone. Drinks were tasty as well. Server Aurora was very friendly and knew the menu well.
I having been going to Hersh's since its inception, the best neopolitan style pizza pants down in Baltimore. Josh the chef and Steff have done a great job.
The carbonara is incredible and the crostini options are always good

Pizza was ok. Not the best neopollitan I've ever had but it was decent. The fried shrimp were below average. The batter and toppings were tasty but the shrimp itself was overcooked. Overall it was over priced. You paid more for the ambiance than anything else.

Awesome food. Easily accommodated my large party on a Saturday with a simple call ahead the week before. Service was prompt and the drinks were cold. Great place for a casual date night or family get together.
4.5 easily. Have been here at least 6 times. Eat in and carry out. Great food. Reasonable prices. Overall friendly staff!

Our dining experience was exceptional.  The staff was friendly and on the ball, checking in frequently to attend our needs but not so frequently as to be annoying. The steamed shrimp were perfect as were the king crab legs. The oysters were cold and salty and the cream of crab soup was hot with an ample serving of crab. Can't wait to go back.

The food, place, and atmosphere was good. Service was awesome. Parking is hard to find but that is expected for the area. My wife and I had the seafood platter and it was good. Also try the Hoop Tea, it is a pretty tasty.

Very clean.... Great staff..... Tried LP Steamers out for the first time today and everything I ate was wonderful.... I will definitely be back and I'm getting crabs. Thanks for such a great experience.

I've lived in Baltimore for 37 years and Anchor Oyster Bar is my FAVORITE restaurant. Plan to wait on the comfy bench outside and enjoy the sights of Castro Street. The seafood is so fresh and delicious. The staff is always friendly and relaxed. Perfect date night. Thank you Anchor Oyster Bar!

Great place wonderful atmosphere and amazing employees. Food can be a bit pricey along with drinks, but what you end up spending more on in money, you will make up for in Good Times. Perfect place to watch any type of football game this time of year, especially Sunday nights when the Baltimore Ravens are playing!!
Drinks were delicious had a great time the food was awesome as you can see I was truly Twisted the drinks the drinks LOL and if you like to shoot pool or if you like karaoke it's a great place to be
Good place to have a drink. The food is tasty especially the chicken Chesapeake sandwich. Just watch out for the rowdy folks that show up.
Cute little bar with good prices on liquor a mean eight bucks for a jolly ranchers is standard. Remember to tip the bartender the dj is nice also and the food is the best part
The food was great. The crab cakes was delicious.

Not a bad hotel. The hotel is nice enough but is dated. The lobby is bright and the staff is very welcoming. Location is great since you are a just a few blocks from the harbor (the only good place in Baltimore) and it's easy to get to other good areas like Fells Point and Mount Vernon.
Overall, ranks pretty low on the list of the very many Marriott hotels I've stayed at. Oh and the restaurant (The Yard) is complete garbage and Marriott should be embarrassed by it enough to make some significant changes.

We always stay at Marriott's because you can count on consistency. I wasn't disappointed. Everything was wonderful, pleasant front desk, clean room, everything you want in a hotel... plus a great location right beside Royal Farms Arena.

Nice hotel that I come to regularly,  quiet rooms and good restaurants in the area.  Staff is nice and helpful if you need something. Close to the Inner Harbor area with lots of things to do and see. Lots of ambulances as there is a hospital close by and the road is a route to the ER I guess.

This was an excellent hotel. Tremendously helpful and friendly staff, and the most comfortable beds you will probably find in any hotel. Good location, but pay attention to your surroundings if you go up Eutaw St.
Best hotel experience I’ve had with Marriott. The bartenders here are exquisite and the concierge were extremely hospitable. Breakfast was really good for a hotel.
Fantastic Thai food! I eat a lot of Thai all over the US. NYC, DC, Philly, Virginia, LA. This is top notch! Baltimore you lucked out!
Had a great experience here. Thai red curry was delicious

If you like Thai food you have to check out this place. The chicken pad Thai was wonderful.  The lunch portion was large enough that my wife and I split it with some appetizers. We were well pleased with our lunch. They are inexpensive for how much food you get.

Our go to Thai place for lunch. The green curry is good, but order extra rice. Pad see wee is good too. Another favorite is the pineapple fried rice. When you order the lunch special, it comes with a small salad.

Fantastic staff, AWESOME gift shop that includes post cards, magnets and a graphic novel written by the director. You can actually see where Poe slept. Many fun fact mentions and very accessible. Not handicapped friendly, but that is due to the architecture. They turned us on to his grave down the way.

Not worth it, go to the grave instead. My kids wanted to look, but they had a reading upstairs and apparently they weren't welcome because (in their excitement) they were talking. Wouldn't let my 10yr old use the bathroom, we walked to the nearest drugstore. So glad my kid got to see guys with guns, a drug deal, step over 'little baggies' and such on the way so he could pee... Never got to see anything beyond the tiny gift shop. We asked for a refund. Will we ever return? The Raven already knows that answer, "Nevermore"

A must-see stop for any Edgar Allan Poe fan! Anyone else might not like it as it is a very small museum for the price you pay. With reading everything and waiting to go upstairs to see his bedroom, it was a total of about 30 minutes (maybe less) spent there. They do have a lot of great stuff in the shop when you go in, so if you are only looking for souvenirs/shopping, you can do so without also paying to go into the house. Please support this place with either buying from the shop, paying to go into the house, or with donations! The staff was very friendly and helpful, too! And no, no restroom. Go to Walgreens a couple of blocks down for that.
An excellent place to visit, just very small. Not a lot to see inside, but what they have preserved is excellent. I appreciated the helpful guides on the tour.

Lets just say it's not a place to visit if your a person of stature. Low ceilings and very narrow stairs. But if you're a fan you probably wouldn't care. Be safe in that area. It's not the safest place to be during certain times a day and night.
The food is outstanding.  My wedding guest did not stop talking about how good the food was.  The service was great and the owner was a pleasure to work with.
Been going there since I was little
Ok food nothing to get excited about
Best cheese steak sub in Baltimore!
Big Ts (Fred's) has been serving nothing but good food here. Been eating here for years and haven't had one negative experience. Happy it's still around after many years
I have been ordering at Big T's Place for 10 + years. The food is always great.

Update- I went back for a second visit during my stay and was delighted to meet Connie. She is so lovely and pleasant. It's so refreshing to meet genuinely nice people. 
This place was a treat to find while I was visiting Baltimore. Connie's Chicken & Waffles is definitely a must if you're in the Monaco area of Baltimore.
Robert was working the restaurant alone and was great. My food was fresh, hot, and delicious. 
I highly recommend this place. 5 stars!

Hands down the best lunch to treat yourself with if you're pulling jury duty - and even if you're not! The standard chicken and waffles did not disappoint: I chose the tenders, which are tough to keep juicy, and they nailed it. Eat it fresh while the waffle is still hot with a delicate baked crust. Consider going back for more. Realize your lunch break is up and run back to the courthouse.

Super delicious chicken! I got the basket with fries instead of waffles, so can't speak to all the flavors of waffles. But the fries were seasoned and delicious and the chicken tenders were huge, delicious, and freshly made.

I was looking forward to trying out the chicken and waffles here. The truth is, there just ok. Not bad not great but ok. The chicken was fried a little to hard for my liking. The waffle was, well, a waffle 🤷🏾‍♀️.  I'm not saying I wouldn't eat here again, I'm just not going out of my way to go there. The servers are nice but I really don't like seeing people on their phones when dealing with customers. In all honesty, you would have to try it for yourself to determine if it's your cup of tea. For me, I'm neutral.

Though I’m originally from Baltimore, I now live down south in North Carolina. My boyfriend and I came back up North for the weekend to visit family and attend a Ravens game and we got hungry for a late night snack in our hotel room so we went on UberEats and ordered from Connie’s. These are some of the best waffles I’ve ever had. I got the Captain Crunch Berry infused waffles with fresh strawberries and maple syrup and my boyfriend got the chicken and waffles. The chicken was so moist and perfectly seasoned. My Captain Crunch waffles threw me straight back into my childhood. The batter was definitely fresh and the waffles turned out perfectly fluffy. To top off the amazing food, the wonderful people who prepared our meals took the time to write “Love Connie” with a smiley face on the top of both boxes. So thank you Connie for making our trip so much sweeter! I would strongly recommend this if you want good old fashioned comfort food prepared by people who genuinely care about the food they are serving!
